 </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE</span><hr size=1> &quot;Edited cause abs cleared up my misunderstanding <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  &quot;<br>
<br>
I've been pretty lucky in resist gear and have very little problems with resists (Frankly, any guild with a few 60 bards shoud have no problem with resists), so it not having resists really doesn't bother me.<br>
<br>
What I personally lack is wisdom.  Even being a high elf, hitting 235+ wis without sacraficing other stats and resists is not easy.  Having 25 wis on my back and not having to give up the 100hp at the same time would totally solve the problem for me.  So this item is worth my points alone for that reason.<br>
<br>
I will admit that for the effort this is kind of lame, but I think thats going to start to become the norm.  They can only let items get so powerful, but they need to continue to provide challenges for the elite guilds.<br>
<br>
Lallail<br>
