<br>
Let me break it down for you as to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  why</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  40 ac</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Nice AC for a back item, sure, but given the softcap it may as well be 0.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  25 stamina</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Sta is capped at 255.  Even the NECROS in my guild are at 255 stamina during raids.  Chances are, if you're a paladin and don't have 255 sta buffed, you're probably still fighting sonic bats and lava duct crawlers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  25 wis/int</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Can't complain about this really.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  100hp</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Of course, the obligatory &quot;uber item&quot; 100hp.  Yahoo.  Read below.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  The effect</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Wow wow wow.  What a complete joke.  Wouldn't be that bad if it stacked with C3, but as it is now, it's laughable.  Someone mentioned &quot;...not always having a chanter following you around for C3...&quot;  Any raid will have at least one, obviously, and with a 4-hour long duration C3, you bet your ass I track someone down for a hit before wandering off to solo.  And yes, all it does is add 250 to your mana pool; no mana regen.<br>
---<br>
<br>
So...<br>
What we have here is a CT cloak with 25 wis.  Don't kid yourselves; that's all it effectively is.  Now factor in the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  TWO MONTHS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> that my guild spent farming timesink keys and weapons to get it.  Guilds who can't even kill ToV dragons can clear fear and drop Cazic Thule in 3-4 hours.  Please.<br>
<br>
Flat out, it needs more HP and might as well have direct mana too.  Give it 10-20 to resists.  Lose this worthless effect and give it something like a 12% mod to avoidance or mitigation. <p><FONT SIZE="1">
